<P>DUE
PREPARATIONS
FOR THE
PLAGUE,
As well for
<HI>SOUL as BODY.</HI></P>
<P>Being &s;ome &s;ea&s;onable THOUGHTS
upon the Vi&s;ible Approach of the
pre&s;ent dreadful CONTAGION in
<HI>France;</HI> the propere&s;t Mea&s;ures to
prevent it, and the great Work of
&s;ubmitting to it.</P>
<BIBL>PSAL. XCI. 10.</BIBL>
<Q>There &s;hall no Evil befal thee, neither
&s;hall the Plague come nigh thy
Dwelling.</Q>
<P><HI>LONDON:</HI>
Printed for E. MATTHEWS, at the <HI>Bible,</HI> and J. BATLEY
at the <HI>Dove</HI> in <HI>Pater-No&s;ter-Row.</HI> MDCCXXII.</P>
