very di&s;con&s;olate, his pious <HI>Si&s;ter,</HI>
who was greatly concern'd for him,
came into his Chamber one Day about
ten Days after the fir&s;t talk with his
<HI>Brother,</HI> where he was fitting very Pen|&s;ive
and Heavy, and began to Comfort
him.</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Si&s;ter.</SPEAKER>
<P>Dear <HI>Brother,</HI> I am very &s;orry
