<P><PB N="263" REF="274">
At the &s;ame time within the Walls of
the City, the Di&s;temper was mo&s;t violent,
too, for notwith&s;tanding the great Number
of People which were rem$v'd from
thence, which was judg'd to be five times
as many, in Proportion to the Numbers of
People, as in the Out-parts; and tho'
in the beginning of <HI>Augu&s;t,</HI> there died
more than twice as many in <HI>Cripplegate</HI>
Pari&s;h only, as died in the whole City,
<HI>viz.</HI> from the fir&s;t of <HI>Augu&s;t</HI> to the
8th.</P>
<LIST>
<LABEL>Buried in <HI>Cripplegate</HI> Pari&s;h</LABEL>
